The Chronicle Oliver Kazunga, Senior Business Reporter THE Standards Association of Zimbabwe (Saz) director general Dr Eve Gadzikwa has been elected to serve on the International Organisation for Standardisation (ISO) Council beginning this year up to 2023. For the past 30 years, Saz has been a member of ISO. “The Standards Association of Zimbabwe director general Dr Eve Gadzikwa has been elected to serve on the International Organisation for Standardisation (ISO) Council from 2021 to 2023. “Active participation in the international standards development ensures that the national economic, social and environmental standardisation strategy of Zimbabwe are considered,” said Saz. – @okazunga